description: Advisor uses a rules-based quantitative model to evaluate U.S. common stocks. Fund invests in stocks that together have the potential to generate lower volatility than the broad U.S. equity market. The portfolio includes a diverse mix of stocks representing many different market capitalizations (large, mid, and small), market sectors, and industry groups. Seeks long-term capital appreciation. Typically, at least 80% of the fund’s assets will be invested in securities issued by U.S. companies.
name: Vanguard U.S. Minimum Volatility ETF
